Rotary Club of Karura held a dinner dance and fashion show at the Golden Tulip Hotel in Nairobi on Saturday evening. On showcase were clothes designed and made by prisoners in Langata Maximum Women&rsquo;s Prison.It sought to raise funds towards the creation of a micro credit fund to support livelihoods of women released from prison.Among the invited guests were Langata Maximum Women&rsquo;s Prison officer-in-charge Olivia Obell, UAP Old Mutual group HR manager Winnie Pertet and Salaries and Renumeration commissioner Anne Owuor.